  "soap_summary": "Likely viral respiratory infection: persistent dry cough (5\u20136 days), rhinorrhea, mild sore throat/throat irritation, chills with possible unconfirmed fever, fatigue and myalgia; brief diarrhea/stomach upset at onset which has resolved. No sputum production, no chest pain, no ear symptoms, no nausea/vomiting, no urinary issues. Past medical history: type 2 diabetes and hypertension (on metformin and lisinopril). Advised self-care, rest, fluids, and regular paracetamol; return if not improving or if breathing worsens.",
